trans-unit.source: Represents an instance key and contains an identifier and metadata associated with the instance key.
An instance key acts as a non-unique alias for an instance.
Initializes an instance of the <xref href="System.Runtime.DurableInstancing.InstanceKey"></xref> class using the GUID associated with the instance key passed.
The GUID associated with the instance key.
Must not be Guid.Empty.
Initializes an instance of the <xref href="System.Runtime.DurableInstancing.InstanceKey"></xref> class using the GUID and metadata associated with the instance key.
The GUID associated with the instance key.
Must not be Guid.Empty.
The dictionary that contains metadata associated with the instance key or null.

Compares the GUID associated with the current object (stored in the <xref:System.Runtime.DurableInstancing.InstanceKey.Value*> property) with the GUID associated with the <xref href="System.Runtime.DurableInstancing.InstanceKey"></xref> object.
An <xref href="System.Runtime.DurableInstancing.InstanceKey"></xref> object that needs to be compared with the current object.
Must not be null.
<xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref> if the objects are same; otherwise returns <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""></xref>.
Returns a unique hash code for the current <xref href="System.Runtime.DurableInstancing.InstanceKey"></xref> objectâ€™s GUID (stored in the Value property).
The unique hash code.
Returns an invalid <xref href="System.Runtime.DurableInstancing.InstanceKey"></xref> object.

An invalid <xref href="System.Runtime.DurableInstancing.InstanceKey"></xref> object has Guid.Empty value for the <xref:System.Runtime.DurableInstancing.InstanceKey.Value*> property and a <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""></xref> value for the <xref:System.Runtime.DurableInstancing.InstanceKey.IsValid*> property.
An invalid instance key.
Gets a value that indicates whether the instance key is valid.
<xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref> if the instance key is valid; otherwise <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""></xref>.
An instance key is valid if and only if its GUID (stored in the Value property) is not Guid.Empty.
Gets the dictionary that contains metadata associated with the instance key.
The dictionary that contains metadata associated with the instance key.
This dictionary is a read-only dictionary.
Gets the GUID value associated with the current instance key.
An instance key is valid if and only if its GUID (stored in the Value property) is not Guid.Empty.
The GUID value associated with the current instance key.
